{
  "texts": [
    "This is the most challenging condition for the within dataset evaluation settings (Deng et al., 2023).",
    "Cross-dataset: Train on a dataset and test on another, to assess cross-domain generalization.",
    "We keep the same 5-fold evaluation protocol across settings for robust performance estimates.",
    "For spatial predictions, we report Negative Log-Likelihood (NLL), to measure how well the model fits observed scan paths, and Normalized Levenshtein Distance (NLD), quantifying alignment quality between predicted and actual sequences.",
    "For temporal predictions, we use NLL t, as NLD considers the distance between spatial sequences (e.g., strings), which does not apply to the temporal dimension."
  ]
}